ProcedureHelp.#cdata:
Syntax: PROC BOXPLOT options ; 
    BY variables ; 
    ID variables ; 
    INSET keywords </options> ; 
    INSETGROUP keywords </ options> ; 
    PLOT analysis-variable*group-variable <(block-variables)> <=symbol-variable> </ options > ; 

The BOXPLOT procedure creates side-by-side box-and-whiskers plots of measurements 
organized in groups. A box-and-whiskers plot displays the mean, quartiles, and 
minimum and maximum observations for a group.

StatementHelp.#cdata:
Syntax: ID variable(s) ;

The ID statement specifies variables used to identify observations. The ID variables 
must be variables in the input data set.
